<br>
Pet canning is nice, but only reallly useful in downtime. Doing it during a battle will cost you damage since your pet is not doing damage anymore. Nor are you for that matter. Probably balances out, but unless it's a really long fight, I don't see it helping all that much during a fight (and is  largely unneccessary).<br>
<br>
Kinelaria<br>
Taeru<br>
Lana <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/udulwin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dulwin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#333333>(9/20/02 12:32:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=352.topic&index=25>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: ...</span><hr size=1> I think that Hogfather hit the point exactly. For a ranger the archery AA is a class defining skill. As such it is appropriate to use it a the gold-standard for class defining AA. VI seemed to have put some thought (albiet only about 5 minutes for some classes) into the AA levels available to all classes. In some cases, as pointed out here and on other class boards, some where way off mark and in some cases are astronomically exspensive to reach while not really benefitting from it much.<br>
<br>
It really sucks when you look at what an AA is and what it is supposed to do only to find out that it doesn't function. A good example is the singing mastery AA for bards. Getting to SM 3 is a long road only when you get there it is not effective b/c VI put a cap on the singing skill to keep it in line. As a result, nerfed an AA that is overpriced and underpowered, similar to frenzied burnout (sounds really nice, except for that AE explosion, wtf were they thinking?).<br>
<br>
All class, imho, are kind of messed up when it comes to AA. There is far too much overlap and a good bit of &quot;why does my class get this as an AA&quot;. I really hope that VI looks at this again.<br>
<br>
And Cheers! to the rangers. The archery AA's are very nice. <p>Dulwin Klangfarbenmelodie<br>Bard of 59 Note-Filled Songs<br>Pround member of Nocturnal Sun - Luclin<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=270840">Look at me!</a></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#333333>- </font><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower>The Magician's Tower</a><font color=#333333> - </font><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32>Class Balance</a> <font color=#333333> - </font><a href="http://www.magecompendium.com/">The Mage Compendium</a><font color=#333333> - </font>  <br><br><table border=0 align=center><tr><td align=center><a href="http://login.ezboard.com/BBSSystem.showUserPaymentScreen" target="_blank">Upgrade your account to ezSupporter...</a></td><td><img src="http://www.ezboard.com/image/spacer.gif" width=15 height=1 border=0></td><td align=center><a href="http://login.ezboard.com/BBSSystem.showUserPaymentScreen" target="_blank">...and never see another ad or pop-up again</a></td></tr></table><CENTER><!-- START BOTTOM AD SCRIPT -->
